    a: "The simplest method is to upload an llms.txt file directly to your WordPress root directory via FTP, SFTP, or your hosting control panel's file manager. The file should be placed at the same level as wp-config.php, making it accessible at yourdomain.com/llms.txt. Alternatively, create a custom WordPress rewrite rule in your .htaccess file to serve a dynamically generated llms.txt from a WordPress endpoint. The static file method is simpler and more reliable for most sites.",
