      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <section id="wordpress-geo-overview" class="anchor-top prose-dark mb-16">
        <h2>WordPress and AI Optimisation: The Opportunity</h2>

        <p>
          <strong>WordPress is the dominant content management system for precisely the type of authoritative, long-form content that AI engines prefer to cite.</strong>
          Publishers, agencies, professional service firms, and B2B brands running WordPress have a structural advantage in AI visibility:
          their content is typically well-organised, editorially rigorous, and hosted on domains with established authority. The problem
          is that most WordPress installations are configured for traditional search, not for AI retrieval.
        </p>

        <p>
          The gap between traditional SEO configuration and GEO-ready configuration on WordPress is bridgeable with a focused
          technical audit and a structured content update programme. Unlike Shopify, WordPress gives you direct access to every
          layer of the stack — file system, server configuration, database, and theme code — which means you can implement the
          full GEO technical setup without workarounds or platform restrictions.
        </p>

        <p>
          GEO for WordPress is part of the broader
          <a href="/geo-by-industry/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">GEO by industry</a>
          framework. The principles of
          <a href="/generative-engine-optimisation/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">generative engine optimisation</a>
          apply across all platforms; this guide covers the WordPress-specific implementation details. The four areas that deliver
          the greatest AI visibility improvement on WordPress are: schema plugin configuration, content structure, technical setup
          (robots.txt and crawler access), and llms.txt deployment.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 2 -->
